ConditionDescription: This saxophone is in very good overall condition for its age. It probably dates from the period 1922–1925, not long before the acquisition by Selmer of the Adolphe Saxe workshop in 1929. It appears to be low-pitched and is the same size as a modern tenor saxophone, with an auxiliary top F key.. It has been re-lacquered at some time and the lacquer remains good.The bell would benefit from roller attention but this is not strictly necessary. There are some white marks at the base of the bell, probably from a saxophone stand. There are a few minor dents which a repairer could blow out and it would benefit from being re-padded. It has no case.
